msContents.summary: Copy of a treatise on Shiʻite rituals and customs. This copy has extensive marginal commentary that creates different shapes on three sides.

msItem.title: Junnat al-amān al-wāqiya wa jannat al-imān al-bāqiya

supportDesc.extent: 358 leaves : 240 x 130 (165 x 70) mm bound to 240 x 135 mm

layoutDesc.layout: 25 lines per page, border-ruled, extensive marginalia.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Naskh in black ink; pointed, partially vocalized.

decoDesc.decoNote: Polychrome (red, blue, yellow) and gold floriated headpiece (f. 1v); suggestion of cloudbands on the first page opening (f. 1v-2); rubrications in red; textblock border-ruled in gold, black, blue; page-opening framed in gold. Some headings are set off in red with gold divider lines above and below.

binding.p: Bound in dark red and black leather with gilt stamped central mandorla, two pendants on the vertical axis, and outer frame; gilt tooled design between the inner and outer frames. Pink paper pastedowns.

origin.p: This copy was completed five years after the scribe returned from the pilgrimage to Mekka (Ḥajj), though no date is recorded (f. 361r).

history.provenance: Several owner's stamps and notes (Flyleaf 1r, in front; f. 1r, 361v).
